===Etymology===
From {{w|Simón Bolívar}}, Venezuelan statesman; Bolívar's own name derives from the village of Bolibar in Spanish Biscay. Its name comes from the {{etyl|eu|en}} [[bolu]] ("windmill") and [[ibar]] ("valley").

